The Australian government.  They probably meant well, but ended up at the centre of a grotesque celebrity farce.   
The Victoria government.  It seems they provided Djokovic with all the help and support he needed to exploit a legal loophole and undermine a key immigration policy of the Australian government.
Tennis Australia.  Lapdogs of wealthy globalist investors.  See Victoria government.
The Australian Open.  A complete shambles.
The Spanish government.  Can unvaccinated celebrities really do as they please in Spain?
The Serbian government.  In all likelihood they were fully aware of Djokovic’s many transgressions, but lacked the courage to do anything about it.  
The Serbian Prime Minister.  What was she thinking of?
No-vax Djokovic.  Spoilt, arrogant, self-obsessed, entitled, petulant and selfish. 
The Professional Tennis Association. They have managed to let down an entire generation of the people they supposedly represent. 
Emirates Airlines.  Can unvaccinated celebrities really fly with Emirates Airlines anywhere they like, at any time they please?

snippet.textDisplay: Novak was in detention because he chose not to leave Australia. The Judge reinstated his Visa because pushy immigration agents denied Novak procedural fairness. The immigration minister, an elected representative, has the authority to determine if the grounds to cancel the Visa outweigh the reasons for not cancelling the Visa. In reality top of mind will be what makes the Liberals look least bad with an election looming. Hitting a ball for profit, being good at tennis, shouldn't make you above the rules.
